<p>As the current leading Layer2 network by total value locked (TVL), Arbitrum''s transaction costs are expected to decrease substantially post-upgrade. According to industry analysis, due to reduced data submission fees, user gas fees on Arbitrum could drop to near-zero levels, attracting more small transactions and everyday users. Regarding performance, Arbitrum''s throughput will benefit from more efficient data processing. Feedback from the developer community suggests transaction confirmation speeds are expected to improve, further solidifying its dominant position in DeFi applications. In the long term, a low-cost environment may encourage the Arbitrum ecosystem to expand from financial applications to diverse scenarios like gaming and social platforms.</p>
