<p>The Cancun upgrade''s impact on the Decentralized Finance (DeFi) ecosystem is profound. The substantial reduction in transaction costs will make DeFi applications more accessible, particularly for retail users. First, lower gas fees may foster the rise of high-frequency trading strategies, such as arbitrage and liquidity mining. According to DeFi Llama statistics, this could increase the total value locked (TVL) in DeFi protocols on Layer2. Second, a low-cost environment encourages the deployment of more complex financial products, such as derivatives and structured products, thereby enriching the DeFi ecosystem. Finally, as Layer2 performance improves, cross-chain interoperability may strengthen, promoting the formation of a multi-chain DeFi landscape and reshaping asset liquidity and yield capture models.</p>
