INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (119, 'S&P 500 vs. Nasdaq Divergence Widens: Tech Stocks Retreat, Is the Market Rotating to Value and Cyclical Sectors?', 's-p-500-vs-nasdaq-divergence-widens-tech-stocks-retreat-is-the-market-rotating-t', 'This article analyzes the recent resilience of the S&P 500 relative to the Nasdaq, exploring whether capital is rotating from high-valuation tech stocks to sectors like financials and industrials amid fluctuating rate expectations, and assesses the sustainability of this potential market style shift.', '<h2>S&P 500 and Nasdaq Divergence Widens: Where is Market Style Headed Amid Tech Stock Pressure?</h2><p>Recently, the U.S. stock market has exhibited a notable divergence. The tech-heavy Nasdaq Composite Index, after hitting record highs, is facing significant downward pressure. Meanwhile, the broader-based S&P 500 Index has shown greater resilience. This divergence in performance has sparked widespread discussion about whether capital is rotating away from high-valuation tech sectors to other areas, prompting investors to reassess how market style might evolve in an environment of persistent volatility in interest rate expectations.</p><h3>Divergence Emerges: Nasdaq Under Pressure, S&P Shows Resilience</h3><p>Entering the second half of the year, the momentum in the <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/news/us-stock">U.S. stock market</a> appears to have shifted subtly. After a strong rally driven by the AI boom, the Nasdaq''s upward momentum has weakened, with signs of profit-taking in some leading tech stocks. In contrast, the S&P 500 has performed relatively steadily. The core of this difference lies in index composition: the Nasdaq is heavily concentrated in large tech companies, while the S&P 500 has a more balanced sector distribution, including traditional sectors like financials, industrials, and healthcare.</p><p>Analysts point out that this divergence suggests the market''s upward momentum may no longer be confined to a handful of tech giants. As investors grow wary of the future growth prospects or current valuation levels of tech stocks, capital is beginning to seek other potential opportunities. According to the CME Group''s FedWatch Tool, market expectations for the Federal Reserve''s future interest rate path remain volatile. This uncertainty amplifies fluctuations in growth stocks, particularly high-valuation tech stocks, as they are more sensitive to the discounting of future cash flows.</p><h3>Sector Rotation Amid Fluctuating Rate Expectations</h3><p>The outlook for Federal Reserve monetary policy is a key variable influencing market style shifts. Although inflation data has moderated, the labor market remains robust, creating uncertainty around the timing and magnitude of rate cuts. Under expectations of "higher for longer" interest rates, interest-rate-sensitive growth stocks are under pressure.</p><p>Reports indicate that some market capital is flowing from richly valued tech stocks to other areas. A clear sign is the recent improved performance in sectors more sensitive to the economic cycle, such as financials and industrials. The financial sector benefits from higher net interest margins, while the industrial sector may gain from manufacturing reshoring and infrastructure spending. Additionally, the energy sector is attracting attention due to geopolitical factors and supply-demand dynamics. If this rotation persists, it could signal a shift in market logic—from pricing a premium for distant future growth to focusing on current earnings, dividends, and relative value.</p><p>The performance of chip stocks, represented by Nvidia (NVDA)—the core engine of the previous AI rally—significantly impacts market sentiment. The stock surged following a strong earnings report but subsequently experienced increased volatility, reflecting investor indecision between chasing the trend and valuation concerns. This may be a microcosm of a potential turning point in market style.</p><h3>Analyzing the Sustainability of the Style Shift</h3><p>Whether the current market style shift can be sustained depends on the confluence of several factors. First, the macroeconomic environment is crucial. If the U.S. economy achieves a "soft landing"—controlling inflation while avoiding a deep recession—cyclical stocks sensitive to the economy would have a stronger foundation for performance, making the rotation more sustainable. Conversely, if the economy slows more than expected, defensive sectors and potentially tech growth stocks could regain favor.</p><p>Second, corporate earnings are the fundamental driver. Capital flows ultimately need fundamental support. If companies in sectors like financials, industrials, and energy can deliver consistently better-than-expected earnings, they will effectively attract and retain capital. According to earnings forecast aggregates from institutions like FactSet, the market is closely watching next-quarter earnings guidance across industries.</p><p>Finally, tech stocks themselves are not monolithic. The long-term industry trend of artificial intelligence remains intact, but the market may be entering a phase of separating the wheat from the chaff, focusing on selective picking. Tech companies with solid performance, clear business models, and reasonable valuations may still weather the cycle. Therefore, the style shift is more likely a rebalancing within the market rather than a simple "abandon tech, embrace traditional" move.</p><h3>Conclusion and Outlook</h3><p>The performance divergence between the S&P 500 and Nasdaq clearly reveals an ongoing market reassessment. In an environment of high and uncertain interest rate paths, the singular logic of growth-stock-driven rallies is being challenged, with capital beginning to uncover broader value. This does not signal the end of the tech stock rally but rather represents a healthy market adjustment and broadening of participation.</p><p>In the coming period, market style may present a "blooming of a hundred flowers" scenario rather than a single dominant theme. Investors need to focus on economic data, Federal Reserve policy signals, and corporate earnings quality, making more balanced allocations between growth and value, cyclical and defensive sectors. The market''s resilience stems precisely from its internal capacity for sector rotation and absorption.</p><p><strong>Risk Warning:</strong> The above market analysis is based on public information and general market views, intended solely for information sharing and discussion, and does not constitute any specific investment advice or trading commitment. Stock market investing carries risks, and market styles can shift rapidly. Investors must make independent judgments and decisions cautiously based on their own risk tolerance. Past performance is not indicative of future results.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute investment advice. Financial markets involve risks; invest with caution. Data and views are current as of the time of writing and may change with market developments.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Begin Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/31536334/pexels-photo-31536334.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 1, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 14:17:40', '2026-04-08 18:25:45', '2026-04-08 18:25:45', '2026-04-08 18:25:45', 'en', 'neutral', 'NVDA', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (120, 'Gold Price Hits Record High! Soaring Gold Options Implied Volatility Serves as Warning, Revealing Market Pricing of Risk and Inflation', 'gold-price-hits-record-high-soaring-gold-options-implied-volatility-serves-as-wa', 'This article analyzes how the derivatives market warns of gold price volatility through movements in gold options implied volatility and open interest. It explores how geopolitical risk and inflation expectations are priced, and how options tools amplify and signal future price trends, offering investors a unique market perspective.', '<h2>Gold Price Soars to Record High, Options Market Sends Strong Warning Signal</h2><p>Recently, the international <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=%E9%BB%84%E9%87%91">gold</a> price has continued to climb, reportedly breaking through its historical high. Echoing the fervor in the spot market, the gold options market has also experienced significant volatility. The key metric measuring market expectations for future price volatility—Implied Volatility (IV)—has shown a notable surge, while the structure of open interest has also exhibited unusual movements. These signals from the derivatives market are revealing deeper market sentiment and underlying risks for investors.</p><h3>Soaring Implied Volatility: The Market is Pricing in Uncertainty</h3><p>Implied volatility is central to options pricing, reflecting the market''s expectation for the future price fluctuation range of the underlying asset. When gold options implied volatility rises rapidly, it typically means traders anticipate more dramatic price swings in the future, and are thus willing to pay a higher premium to purchase options for hedging risk or directional speculation.</p><p>The surge in implied volatility this time is closely linked to multiple overlapping factors. Firstly, geopolitical tensions persist, with reports indicating no signs of easing in regional conflicts in some areas, prompting capital to flow into gold, a traditional safe-haven asset. Secondly, inflation data from major global economies remains stubborn, with market concerns over long-term inflation expectations providing support for gold prices. Furthermore, the monetary policy paths of major central banks, especially the outlook for the Federal Reserve''s interest rate decisions, remains a sword of Damocles hanging over the market. The options market, through soaring implied volatility, is collectively pricing in these macro uncertainties.</p><h3>Unusual Open Interest Movements: Bullish Sentiment Coexists with Risk Hedging</h3><p>Beyond implied volatility, changes in options Open Interest also convey important information. Reports indicate that as the gold price broke through previous highs, open interest in deep out-of-the-money call options increased significantly. These options are relatively cheap and are often used to speculate on extreme upward moves in gold prices. The growth in their open interest reflects strong bullish sentiment and speculative demand among some market participants.</p><p>Simultaneously, the distribution of open interest across different strike prices and expiration dates reveals a complex market structure. Open interest in near-month at-the-money and slightly out-of-the-money options is also quite dense, suggesting substantial capital is engaged in short-term directional trading or risk hedging. Institutional investors may be constructing options portfolios (such as straddles or strangles) to prepare for potential large two-way swings in gold prices, whether upward or downward. This open interest structure indicates that the market consensus is not simply a one-sided bullish bet, but rather a widespread expectation that high volatility will persist.</p><h3>Derivatives: Amplifiers and Early Warning Systems for Volatility</h3><p>Derivative instruments like gold options have played a dual role in this market movement. On one hand, they are "amplifiers" of volatility. The influx of significant capital into the options market for speculation or hedging influences liquidity expectations and the price discovery process for the underlying asset through its trading activity itself, potentially exacerbating short-term volatility in the spot market. For example, options market makers, to hedge the risk exposure from selling options, need to perform dynamic hedging operations in the spot or futures markets. This "Gamma hedging" behavior can create a momentum effect, buying on rallies and selling on declines, during rapid market moves.</p><p>On the other hand, the options market serves as a crucial "early warning system." Implied volatility, as a forward-looking indicator, often leads actual volatility in the spot market. Its sudden and sustained surge is a signal warranting caution, hinting that a potential price inflection point or volatility event may be approaching. Abnormal concentrations in open interest act like a "heat map" of market sentiment, clearly marking the key price levels and time windows anticipated by most traders, providing a window into the focal points of market bull-bear battles.</p><h3>Outlook: Monitoring Volatility Reversion and the Macro Narrative</h3><p>Currently, the gold market is in a complex phase where macro narratives (safe-haven demand, inflation) intertwine with technical factors from the derivatives market. The key to future price action may lie in whether implied volatility can recede from its highs, and how it does so. If the gold price consolidates at high levels before choosing a new direction, volatility may remain elevated or spike again. If macro uncertainties diminish and gold price fluctuations narrow, volatility will gradually revert to its mean, and option prices will decline accordingly.</p><p>Investors need to closely monitor upcoming macroeconomic data releases, such as US inflation and employment reports, as well as policy statements from major central banks. These factors will directly influence market judgments on real interest rates and the US dollar''s trajectory, thereby determining gold''s long-term appeal. Concurrently, changes in options market open interest and the structure of the volatility surface (Volatility Smile/Skew) will continue to provide real-time clues for gauging short-term market sentiment and risk.</p><p><strong>Risk Warning:</strong> The above market analysis is based on public information and derivatives data performance, intended to provide informational reference and does not constitute any specific investment advice or trading basis. Financial markets, especially derivatives markets, carry high risks with intense price volatility. Investors should make independent judgments and prudent decisions based on their own risk tolerance.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute any investment advice. Financial markets involve risks; invest with caution. Data and views herein are as of the time of writing and may change with market developments.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/35530434/pexels-photo-35530434.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 3, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 14:17:39', '2026-04-08 18:26:36', '2026-04-08 18:26:36', '2026-04-08 18:26:36', 'en', 'bullish', '', '', 'YayaNews', '', 'commodity', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (121, 'Bitcoin Plunges After Briefly Topping $70K: Institutional Flows Reveal Market Divisions and Future Trajectory', 'bitcoin-plunges-after-briefly-topping-70k-institutional-flows-reveal-market-divi', 'This article analyzes the macro sentiment and institutional positioning shifts behind Bitcoin''s sharp volatility, exploring the tension between short-term technical pullbacks and the long-term bull narrative to uncover the roots of market division and the focus of capital flows.', '<h2><a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=%E6%AF%94%E7%89%B9%E5%B8%81">Bitcoin</a> Rides a Rollercoaster, Briefly Surpassing Then Losing the $70K Milestone</h2><p>The cryptocurrency market has recently experienced intense volatility. After successfully breaking through the significant psychological barrier of $70,000, the price of Bitcoin failed to hold its ground and subsequently underwent a sharp correction. According to CoinGecko data, this sudden price drop occurred against a backdrop of generally optimistic market sentiment and substantial capital inflows, highlighting the fierce battle between bullish and bearish forces in the current market. The dramatic price swings not only unsettle retail investors but also reveal subtle shifts in institutional capital flows and emerging divisions in market consensus.</p><h2>Macro Sentiment and Institutional Holdings: The Root of Market Division</h2><p>The core narrative driving Bitcoin''s recent surge past $70,000 remains the global macroeconomic environment and the continued acceptance by mainstream institutions. The market widely believes that expectations for a shift in monetary policy by major central banks and the sustained net inflows into spot Bitcoin ETFs form the foundation of this bull run. However, the sharp price drop indicates that this optimism is not monolithic.</p><p>Reports suggest that some institutional investors chose to take profits after prices hit new highs, increasing short-term selling pressure. Simultaneously, on-chain data analysis shows that activity in addresses of large holders (often referred to as "whales") became unusually active near the price peak, with both accumulation and distribution occurring. This directly reflects a divergence in outlook among institutions themselves. Some analysts point out that uncertainties in traditional financial markets, such as geopolitical tensions or fluctuating inflation data, may also prompt some risk capital to temporarily exit the more volatile crypto assets in search of safer havens.</p><h3>Tension Between Short-Term Technical Pressure and the Long-Term Narrative</h3><p>From a technical analysis perspective, Bitcoin often faces pressure for a technical correction after a rapid ascent. The area around $70,000 has accumulated significant historical sell-side pressure and recent profit-taking, forming a natural resistance zone. The sharp price drop can be seen as a normal market reaction to this resistance level and a correction to the preceding rapid rally.</p><p>However, a deeper tension exists between short-term technical adjustments and the long-term fundamental narrative. The long-term narrative—encompassing Bitcoin''s halving cycle effects, its growing recognition as "digital <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=%E9%BB%84%E9%87%91">gold</a>," and the global digitization of the financial system—is still held by many steadfast believers. Yet, short-term price volatility is heavily influenced by market sentiment, leverage liquidations, and derivatives market activity. This tension causes the market to oscillate between expectations of "buying the dip" and "trend reversal," exacerbating volatility.</p><h2>Capital Flows Reveal the Focus of Future Market Contests</h2><p>The direction of institutional capital flows is a key indicator for gauging market sentiment. Reports indicate that despite the price correction, some spot Bitcoin ETFs continued to record net inflows, suggesting that some institutional investors view this pullback as an opportunity to build positions. On the other hand, changes in open interest and funding rates in the futures market show that leveraged long positions suffered a degree of unwinding during the sharp decline. While this may contribute to market health, it could also dampen short-term upward momentum.</p><p>Market analysts note that future contests may focus on several areas: first, whether upcoming macroeconomic data and central bank policy signals will strengthen or weaken Bitcoin''s "inflation hedge" narrative; second, any new regulatory developments, especially in major markets; and third, whether the depth and breadth of participation by traditional financial institutions (such as banks and asset managers) in the crypto ecosystem will continue to expand. These factors will collectively influence long-term asset allocation decisions by institutional capital.</p><h2>Risk Disclosure</h2><p>The above market analysis is for reference only, based on publicly available information, and does not constitute any investment advice. The cryptocurrency market is highly volatile, and prices can fluctuate dramatically due to various unpredictable factors such as market sentiment, regulatory policies, and technical issues. Before making any decisions, investors should fully understand the associated risks and make independent judgments based on their own financial situation and risk tolerance.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute investment advice. Financial markets involve risks; invest with caution. Data and opinions are current as of the time of writing and are subject to change with market conditions.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/17755151/pexels-photo-17755151.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 2, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 14:17:35', '2026-04-08 18:27:18', '2026-04-08 18:27:18', '2026-04-08 18:27:18', 'en', 'neutral', 'BTC', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (122, 'Starbucks Launches Energy-Enhanced Fruit Tea Series: Targeting Functional Beverage Market to Boost SBUX Stock?', 'starbucks-launches-energy-enhanced-fruit-tea-series-targeting-functional-beverag', 'Starbucks introduces energy-enhanced fruit tea drinks to expand consumption scenarios and attract younger customers. This article analyzes its strategic response to market trends, product potential, competitive landscape, and implications for U.S. stock investors.', '<h2>Starbucks Menu Innovation: Energy-Enhanced Fruit Tea Series Lands in North American Market</h2><p>Global coffee chain giant Starbucks recently announced it will introduce a series of energy-enhanced fruit tea beverages to its North American store menus. Market observers view this move as a strategic adjustment by the company to attract a broader consumer base, particularly younger customers seeking functional beverages, in an increasingly competitive drinks market. According to reports, the new products aim to combine Starbucks'' classic fruit tea base with natural caffeine or other energy components, offering a refreshing alternative beyond traditional coffee drinks.</p><h3>Strategic Layout in Response to Market Changes and Consumption Trends</h3><p>In recent years, the functional beverage market has grown significantly. Consumers, especially Millennials and Gen Z, have shown rising demand for drinks that combine taste with health benefits. Competition is particularly fierce in the energy drink and tea beverage sectors containing natural energizing ingredients. Starbucks'' launch of energy-enhanced fruit tea is seen as a direct response to this consumption trend, aiming to capture a share of the fast-growing functional ready-to-drink market while consolidating its coffee dominance.</p><p>Analysts point out that this move may help Starbucks attract customers during afternoon hours and non-traditional coffee consumption periods, boosting per-store sales. Facing multiple competitors from other specialty coffee brands, tea shops, and energy drink companies, menu diversification has become one of Starbucks'' key strategies to maintain growth momentum.</p><h3>Product Positioning and Potential Market Impact</h3><p>The newly launched energy-enhanced fruit tea series is expected to build upon Starbucks'' existing "Refreshers" fruit tea product line. This series has been quite popular in the summer market with its vibrant colors and fruit flavors. By adding energy components, Starbucks likely hopes to transform this seasonally strong product into a year-round, functionally positioned daily choice.</p><p>If this product expansion proves successful in the market, it could positively impact Starbucks'' same-store sales and brand appeal. In the food and beverage industry, successful product innovation is often a key driver of stock performance. Starbucks needs continuous product iteration to meet investor expectations for growth and market share.</p><h3>Challenges and Competitive Environment</h3><p>Despite clear strategic intent, Starbucks faces challenges in this new domain. The functional beverage market already has numerous established brands with high consumer loyalty. Starbucks needs to clearly communicate the unique selling points of its new products, such as natural ingredient sources or distinctive flavor combinations, to differentiate them from traditional energy drinks.</p><p>Additionally, supply chain management and cost control are crucial. Introducing new ingredients and production lines may test operational efficiency. The macroeconomic environment, such as changes in consumer disposable income and inflationary pressures, could also affect sales performance of such non-essential consumer goods.</p><h3>What It Means for Investors</h3><p>For investors following Starbucks, menu innovation is an important window to assess the company''s long-term innovation capability and market adaptability. Successful product launches can not only contribute directly to revenue but also enhance brand vitality and attract new customer segments. The market will closely monitor initial sales data and customer feedback for the new series as indicators to judge Starbucks'' future growth potential.</p><p>From a broader perspective, Starbucks'' move also reflects a common trend in the consumer goods industry: leading companies are seeking new growth curves through product functionalization and scenario expansion. In the <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/news/us-stock">U.S. stock</a> market, companies that successfully execute such strategies often command valuation premiums.</p><h3>Risk Disclosure</h3><p>The above content is based on public market information and industry trend analysis, for reference only, and does not constitute any investment advice. Financial markets carry risks; investors should make decisions based on their independent judgment and be mindful of investment risks.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article synthesizes content from public information sources such as RSS feeds. It is for informational purposes only and does not constitute any investment advice. Financial markets involve risks; invest with caution. Data and opinions are current as of publication and may change with market conditions.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/20445467/pexels-photo-20445467.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 1, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 14:17:35', '2026-04-08 18:27:57', '2026-04-08 18:27:57', '2026-04-08 18:27:57', 'en', 'neutral', 'SBUX', '', 'Seeking Alpha', 'https://seekingalpha.com/news/4572852-starbucks-adds-energy-boosted-refreshers-to-menu?utm_source=feed_news_all&utm_medium=referral&feed_item_type=news', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
