n-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute any investment advice. Financial markets carry risks; invest with caution. The data and opinions herein are current as of the time of writing and may change with market developments.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/28894832/pexels-photo-28894832.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 2, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 12:47:33', '2026-04-08 18:45:56', '2026-04-08 18:45:56', '2026-04-08 18:45:56', 'en', 'bullish', 'ETH', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (161, 'Why Did the Nasdaq Hit a Record High? A Deep Dive into the Dual Engine of AI and Consumer Electronics', 'why-did-the-nasdaq-hit-a-record-high-a-deep-dive-into-the-dual-engine-of-ai-and', 'The Nasdaq Composite Index has broken through its all-time high, led by tech heavyweights like Nvidia and Apple. This article analyzes how AI chip demand, expectations for a consumer electronics recovery, and shifting macro conditions are driving the current tech bull market, while also highlighting potential risks.', '<h2>Why Did the Nasdaq Hit a Record High? The Logic Behind the Tech Rally</h2><p>Amid recent market volatility, the Nasdaq Composite Index has once again taken center stage, successfully breaking through its historical peak. This milestone rally is no coincidence; it is driven by multiple structural factors, particularly the strong momentum exhibited by the technology sector, which is centered on artificial intelligence and consumer electronics.</p><h3>Strong Performance from Heavyweights, AI Narrative Remains Dominant</h3><p>In this rally, tech giants like Nvidia (NVDA) and Apple (AAPL) have made significant contributions. As a leader in AI chips, Nvidia''s market performance is closely tied to expectations for the expansion of the AI industry. Reports indicate that as global tech companies continue to ramp up investment in data centers and AI model training, demand for high-performance computing chips remains robust, providing strong support for Nvidia''s earnings outlook.</p><p>Meanwhile, Apple, as a benchmark in consumer electronics and its ecosystem, has seen its stock price reflect market anticipation for its upcoming product refresh cycle, its services business, and potential integration of AI hardware. Market analysts widely believe the consumer electronics industry may be on the cusp of a new wave of upgrade demand, boosting confidence across the related supply chain.</p><h3>Shifts in the Macro Environment and Market Expectations</h3><p>Beyond individual stock factors, changes in macroeconomic expectations have also provided a relatively favorable environment for tech stocks. Despite persistent inflationary pressures, market expectations for a shift in monetary policy by major central banks have, to some extent, alleviated the valuation pressure faced by high-growth tech stocks. Lower expected long-term interest rates help increase the present value of future cash flows, a factor to which R&D-intensive, long-profit-cycle tech companies are particularly sensitive.</p><p>Furthermore, corporate earnings resilience has exceeded expectations. Based on information from the recent earnings season, the revenue and profit performance of major tech companies has been generally solid, with some even providing optimistic guidance. This directly counters previous market concerns that an economic slowdown could severely erode tech company profits.</p><h3>AI and Consumer Electronics: A Dual-Engine Future</h3><p>Looking deeper, the core logic of this rally lies in the dual-engine expectations of "AI empowerment" and "consumer recovery." Artificial intelligence has moved from concept to large-scale commercial application and is reshaping the entire technology industry chain, from cloud computing and software development to hardware manufacturing. This transformative force is seen as a long-term growth engine.</p><p>On the other hand, the consumer electronics market is showing signs of recovery after a period of weakness. Iterations of new products and technologies, such as in PCs, smartphones, and wearables, are expected to stimulate replacement demand. The market anticipates that the deep integration of AI features with end-user devices will be key to driving the next wave of consumer enthusiasm.</p><h3>Potential Risks and Market Outlook</h3><p>Despite the optimistic outlook, investors must remain aware of potential risks. Tech stock valuations are already at historically high levels. Any signals of slower-than-expected AI commercialization, a slowdown in corporate capital expenditure, or deteriorating macroeconomic data could trigger market volatility and sector adjustments. Additionally, geopolitical risks and changes in industry regulatory policies are uncertainties that cannot be ignored.</p><p>Overall, the Nasdaq''s record high represents a concentrated vote of confidence by the market in the long-term growth potential of the tech industry, particularly in AI and consumer electronics. Its sustainability will ultimately depend on whether related companies can translate their technological advantages into tangible profit growth.</p><p><strong>Risk Warning:</strong> The above content is based on public information and analysis, intended for market discussion only, and does not constitute any form of investment advice. The stock market carries risks; investment requires caution. Investors should make independent judgments based on their own circumstances and bear the corresponding risks.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute investment advice. Financial markets involve risks; investment requires caution. The data and views herein are as of the time of publication and may change with market conditions.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/18069813/pexels-photo-18069813.png?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 1, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 12:47:28', '2026-04-08 18:46:03', '2026-04-08 18:46:03', '2026-04-08 18:46:03', 'en', 'bullish', 'NVDA,AAPL', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (162, 'Why Did the Nasdaq Hit a Record High? A Deep Dive into the Dual Engines of AI and Consumer Electronics', 'why-did-the-nasdaq-hit-a-record-high-a-deep-dive-into-the-dual-engines-of-ai-and', 'The Nasdaq Composite has surged to a new all-time high, led by tech heavyweights like Nvidia and Apple. This article analyzes how AI chip demand, expectations for a consumer electronics recovery, and shifting macro conditions are fueling the tech rally, while also highlighting potential risks.', '<h2>Why Did the Nasdaq Hit a Record High? The Logic Behind the Tech Rally</h2><p>Amid recent market volatility, the Nasdaq Composite Index has once again taken center stage, successfully breaking through its previous all-time high. This milestone rally is no coincidence; it is driven by multiple structural factors, particularly the powerful momentum exhibited by the technology sector, with artificial intelligence and consumer electronics at its core.</p><h3>Strong Performance from Heavyweights, AI Narrative Remains Dominant</h3><p>In this rally, tech giants like Nvidia (NVDA) and Apple (AAPL) have made significant contributions. As the leader in AI chips, Nvidia''s market performance is closely tied to expectations for the expansion of the AI industry. Reports indicate that as global tech companies continue to ramp up investments in data centers and AI model training, demand for high-performance computing chips remains robust, providing strong support for Nvidia''s earnings outlook.</p><p>Meanwhile, Apple, as a benchmark in consumer electronics and its ecosystem, has seen its stock price reflect market anticipation for its upcoming product refresh cycle, its services business, and potential integration of AI hardware. Market analysts widely believe the consumer electronics industry may be on the cusp of a new wave of upgrade demand, boosting confidence across the related supply chain.</p><h3>Shifting Macro Environment and Market Expectations</h3><p>Beyond individual stock factors, changes in macroeconomic expectations have also provided a relatively favorable environment for tech stocks. Despite persistent inflationary pressures, market expectations for a shift in monetary policy by major central banks have somewhat alleviated the valuation pressure faced by high-growth tech stocks. Lower expected long-term interest rates help increase the present value of future cash flows, a factor to which R&D-intensive, long-profit-cycle tech companies are particularly sensitive.</p><p>Furthermore, corporate earnings resilience has exceeded expectations. Based on information from the recent earnings season, the revenue and profit performance of major tech companies has been generally solid, with some even providing optimistic guidance. This directly counters previous market concerns that an economic slowdown could severely erode tech sector profits.</p><h3>AI and Consumer Electronics: A Dual-Engine Future</h3><p>Looking deeper, the core logic of this rally lies in the dual-engine expectations of "AI empowerment" and "consumer recovery." Artificial intelligence has moved from concept to large-scale commercial application, reshaping the entire technology industry chain from cloud computing and software development to hardware manufacturing. This transformative force is seen as a long-term growth engine.</p><p>On the other hand, the consumer electronics market is showing signs of recovery after a period of weakness. Iterations of new products and technologies, such as in personal computers, smartphones, and wearable devices, are expected to stimulate replacement demand. The market anticipates that the deep integration of AI capabilities with end-user devices will be key to driving the next wave of consumer enthusiasm.</p><h3>Potential Risks and Market Outlook</h3><p>Despite the optimistic outlook, investors must remain mindful of potential risks. Tech stock valuations are already at historically high levels. Any signals of slower-than-expected AI commercialization, a slowdown in corporate capital expenditure, or deteriorating macroeconomic data could trigger market volatility and sector adjustments. Additionally, geopolitical risks and changes in industry regulatory policies are uncertainties that cannot be ignored.</p><p>Overall, the Nasdaq''s record high represents a concentrated vote of confidence by the market in the long-term growth potential of the technology sector, particularly in AI and consumer electronics. Its sustainability will ultimately depend on whether related companies can translate their technological advantages into tangible profit growth.</p><p><strong>Risk Warning:</strong> The above content is based on public information and analysis, intended for market discussion only, and does not constitute any form of investment advice. The stock market involves risks; investment requires caution. Investors should make independent judgments based on their own circumstances and bear the corresponding risks.</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute investment advice. Financial markets carry risks; investment requires caution. Data and opinions are current as of the time of writing and may change with market developments.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay offers secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/18069813/pexels-photo-18069813.png?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 1, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'standard', 0, '2026-04-07 12:47:28', '2026-04-08 18:46:30', '2026-04-08 18:46:30', '2026-04-08 18:46:30', 'en', 'bullish', 'NVDA,AAPL', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
INSERT INTO articles (id, title, slug, summary, content, cover_image, category_id, topic_id, parent_id, author, status, article_type, view_count, published_at, created_at, updated_at, collected_at, lang, sentiment, tickers, key_points, source, source_url, subcategory, audit_status) VALUES (163, 'Ethereum Layer2 Ecosystem Explodes: Arbitrum and Optimism TVL Surges, DeFi and NFTs See New Opportunities', 'ethereum-layer2-ecosystem-explodes-arbitrum-and-optimism-tvl-surges-defi-and-nft', 'A deep dive into Ethereum Layer2 scaling solutions, comparing data and technical approaches of leading projects like Arbitrum and Optimism, and exploring their long-term impact and investment potential for DeFi and NFT ecosystems.', '<h2><a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=Ethereum">Ethereum</a> Layer2 Ecosystem Explodes: A New Era of Scaling</h2><p>In the cryptocurrency space, Ethereum has long held a leadership position as a smart contract platform, but network congestion and high transaction fees have consistently been bottlenecks hindering ecosystem growth. In recent years, Layer2 scaling solutions have emerged as a key breakthrough. Particularly, Optimistic Rollup projects represented by Arbitrum and Optimism have seen their Total Value Locked (TVL) surge according to reports, signaling that the Ethereum ecosystem is entering a new phase centered on scalability and low cost. This not only alleviates pressure on the mainnet but also fuels explosive growth in applications like Decentralized Finance (DeFi) and Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs). This article provides an in-depth analysis of the current state of Ethereum scaling solutions, compares data, technical paths, and ecosystem development of mainstream Layer2 projects, and looks ahead to their long-term impact.</p><h2>The State of Ethereum Scaling Solutions: Evolution from Main Chain to Layer2</h2><p>Since its inception, Ethereum has been praised for its decentralization and security, but scalability challenges have become increasingly prominent. With the rise of DeFi and NFT applications, network transaction volume has skyrocketed, leading to soaring Gas fees and transaction delays, prompting users and developers to urgently seek more efficient alternatives. To address this issue, the Ethereum community has proposed various scaling paths, primarily including on-chain scaling (like sharding technology) and off-chain scaling (like Layer2). Among these, Layer2 technology builds a second-layer network on top of the Ethereum main chain, moving a large volume of transaction processing off-chain and ultimately anchoring the results back to the main chain, thereby achieving increased throughput and reduced costs.</p><p>Currently, Layer2 solutions are mainly divided into two categories: Optimistic Rollups and ZK Rollups. Optimistic Rollups are based on an "optimistic" assumption, defaulting all transactions as valid and only verifying them in case of disputes, making them suitable for general smart contract scenarios. ZK Rollups utilize zero-knowledge proof technology to generate proofs of transaction validity off-chain before submitting them to the main chain, offering stronger security guarantees. Although ZK Rollups are more advanced technically, Optimistic Rollups have achieved large-scale adoption first due to their compatibility and ease of deployment. According to industry analysis, Ethereum''s scaling roadmap is evolving from a transitional phase dominated by Optimistic Rollups towards a future that integrates ZK Rollups.</p><h3>Technical Path Comparison: Core Differences Between Arbitrum and Optimism</h3><p>Within the Optimistic Rollup camp, Arbitrum and Optimism are two of the most representative projects, each with its own technical focus. Arbitrum, developed by Offchain Labs, employs a multi-round interactive dispute resolution mechanism. When a transaction dispute arises, the system validates it through multiple rounds of challenges and responses, which helps reduce on-chain computational burden and enhances compatibility. Reports indicate that Arbitrum''s design emphasizes high compatibility with the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM), allowing developers to seamlessly migrate existing applications and lowering the barrier to ecosystem migration.</p><p>Optimism, driven by the Optimism Collective, uses a single-round dispute resolution mechanism where disputes are handled directly on-chain, resulting in a simpler structure. Its technical path emphasizes efficiency and predictability, optimizing transaction batching to reduce latency. According to disclosures from the development team, Optimism also incorporates a "fraud proof" mechanism to ensure network security. From a technical perspective, Arbitrum leans towards achieving flexibility through complex mechanisms, while Optimism pursues minimalist design to enhance performance. These two paths reflect different strategies in Layer2 solutions when balancing security, cost, and user experience.</p><p>Furthermore, other Layer2 projects like zkSync and StarkWare, based on ZK Rollup technology, are also developing rapidly, but this article focuses on the Optimistic Rollup solutions that have already achieved an ecosystem explosion. In terms of market adoption, Arbitrum and Optimism, with their early entry advantage, have accumulated significant TVL and user bases.</p><h2>Data Performance: Surging Total Value Locked Reveals Market Confidence</h2><p>Total Value Locked (TVL) is a key metric for gauging the health of the DeFi ecosystem, reflecting the total value of assets users have deposited into protocols. Recently, TVL for Arbitrum and Optimism has reportedly surged significantly, becoming a hot topic in the cryptocurrency market. According to DeFiLlama data, Arbitrum''s TVL has climbed from relatively low levels to significantly higher levels over the past year, at one point becoming the largest Layer2 network on Ethereum; Optimism followed closely, with its TVL also experiencing multiple-fold growth. This surge trend is not accidental but driven by various factors, including high Ethereum mainnet fees, maturation of Layer2 technology, and diversification of ecosystem applications.</p><p>Specifically, TVL growth primarily stems from the migration of DeFi protocols and the deployment of new projects. For example, Decentralized Exchanges (DEXs) and lending platforms on Layer2 offer lower fees and faster transaction confirmations, attracting a large number of users. Community feedback indicates that the number of active addresses and transaction volume on Arbitrum and Optimism networks have also risen simultaneously, suggesting increased user participation. It is noteworthy that TVL growth correlates with overall cryptocurrency market trends; for instance, during periods of <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=Bitcoin">Bitcoin</a> and Ethereum price volatility, Layer2 networks have shown greater resilience, becoming venues for capital hedging and value appreciation.</p><p>Regarding data sources, besides DeFiLlama, platforms like CoinGecko also provide similar TVL tracking, but these figures should be viewed as dynamic indicators rather than precise predictions. Investors should note that TVL can be influenced by market sentiment, technical upgrades, and regulatory events. Overall, the surge in TVL for Arbitrum and Optimism reflects growing market confidence in Ethereum scaling solutions and lays the groundwork for further ecosystem development.</p><h2>Ecosystem Development: A Landscape of Prosperity in DeFi and NFTs</h2><p>The explosion of the Layer2 ecosystem is evident not only in data but also in practical applications. Arbitrum and Optimism have become crucial deployment platforms for DeFi and NFT projects, driving prosperity across the entire cryptocurrency ecosystem.</p><h3>Deep Integration in the DeFi Ecosystem</h3><p>In the DeFi space, Layer2 networks unlock more innovative possibilities by reducing transaction costs and increasing speed. Numerous well-known protocols have emerged on Arbitrum and Optimism, such as:</p><ul><li><strong>Decentralized Exchanges (DEXs)</strong>: Platforms like Uniswap and SushiSwap have deployed on Arbitrum and Optimism, providing users with efficient token swapping services. User reports indicate that transaction fees on these DEXs on Layer2 are a fraction of those on the Ethereum mainnet, promoting high-frequency trading and liquidity provision.</li><li><strong>Lending Platforms</strong>: Protocols like Aave and Compound have also expanded to Layer2, allowing users to borrow, lend, and engage in yield farming at lower costs. This lowers the barrier to entry for DeFi, attracting more retail investors.</li><li><strong>Derivatives and Stablecoins</strong>: Synthetic asset protocols and stablecoin projects are testing new features on Layer2, enhancing the accessibility of financial products.</li></ul><p>These integrations not only improve user experience but also foster cross-protocol collaboration. For example, through Layer2 bridging technology, assets can flow freely between the Ethereum main chain and Layer2 networks, improving capital efficiency. Industry observations suggest that DeFi activity is gradually migrating from the mainnet to Layer2, forming a multi-layered, interoperable ecosystem.</p><h3>Innovation Wave in the NFT Space</h3><p>The NFT market also benefits from Layer2 scaling. High Gas fees once limited NFT creation and trading, but Layer2 provides a low-cost environment, spurring a new wave of digital art and collectibles. On Arbitrum and Optimism, NFT marketplaces like sidechain versions of OpenSea and emerging platforms are rising, supporting faster minting and trading.</p><p>For instance, NFT creators can mint works at lower costs on Layer2, while collectors enjoy seamless trading experiences. Reports indicate that some NFT projects have prioritized Layer2 as their launch platform to reduce user entry barriers. Furthermore, Layer2 facilitates the integration of NFTs with DeFi, such as NFT-collateralized lending and fractionalized trading, further expanding application scenarios.</p><p>Ecosystem development extends beyond the technical layer to include community building and governance. Both Arbitrum and Optimism have launched native tokens (like ARB and OP) for incentivizing participation and decentralized governance. This enhances user stickiness and drives long-term protocol evolution. Overall, the prosperity of the Layer2 ecosystem injects new vitality into Ethereum, helping it maintain a leading position in competition.</p><h2>Long-Term Impact: Reshaping the Future Landscape of Cryptocurrency</h2><p>The explosion of the Ethereum Layer2 ecosystem holds not only short-term market significance but also the potential for profound long-term impact on the cryptocurrency industry. Analyzing from technical, economic, and community dimensions, Layer2 will drive the transformation of the Ethereum and broader blockchain ecosystem.</p><h3>Technical Impact: Enhanced Scalability and Interoperability</h3><p>Layer2 technology marks a significant breakthrough in blockchain scalability. By moving transaction processing off-chain, the Ethereum mainnet can focus on security and decentralization, while Layer2 networks handle efficient execution. This division of labor and collaboration model could serve as a blueprint for future multi-chain architectures. Long-term, as technologies like ZK Rollup mature, Layer2 may integrate with Ethereum sharding to build a seamless, high-throughput global computing platform.</p><p>Moreover, Layer2 promotes cross-chain interoperability. Through bridging protocols, assets and data can flow between different Layer2 networks and public chains, forming an interconnected ecosystem. This helps break down silos and enhance the overall utility of blockchain. For example, a user might use DeFi protocols on Arbitrum while trading NFTs on Optimism without frequently switching networks.</p><h3>Economic Impact: Adoption and Innovation in DeFi and NFTs</h3><p>From an economic perspective, Layer2''s low-cost environment will accelerate the adoption of DeFi and NFTs. Traditional finance users may be more willing to try DeFi if transaction fees are manageable; similarly, NFTs can expand into more areas like gaming, identity verification, and supply chains. Industry forecasts suggest Layer2 could increase Ethereum''s daily transaction volume by an order of magnitude, thereby attracting more institutional capital and developers.</p><p>Long-term, the Layer2 ecosystem may give rise to new business models. For instance, micro-payments and subscription services based on Layer2 could become commonplace, or more hybrid applications combining AI and blockchain may emerge. Increased economic activity will also enhance the value of the Ethereum network,</p><div class="disclaimer" style="margin-top:2em;padding:1em 1.2em;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(100,116,139,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(100,116,139,0.2);font-size:0.8em;color:#94a3b8;"><p><strong>Disclaimer</strong></p><p>This article is for informational purposes only and does not constitute any investment advice. Financial markets carry risks; invest with caution. Data and opinions are current as of publication and may change with market developments.</p></div><div class="cta-block" style="margin-top:1em;padding:1.5em;border-radius:12px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(59,130,246,0.1),rgba(16,185,129,0.1));border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,0.2);"><p><strong>Start Your Trading Journey</strong></p><p>Yayapay provides secure and convenient global asset trading services.<a href="https://invest.biyapay.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color:#3b82f6;font-weight:bold;"> Register Now →</a></p></div>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/31829081/pexels-photo-31829081.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&h=650&w=940', 2, NULL, NULL, 'YayaNews', 'published', 'deep', 0, '2026-04-07 12:18:38', '2026-04-08 18:47:15', '2026-04-08 18:47:15', '2026-04-08 18:47:15', 'en', 'bullish', 'ETH', '', 'YayaNews', '', '', 'approved') ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
