l but driven by multiple factors, including high Ethereum mainnet fees, maturation of Layer2 technology, and diversification of ecosystem applications.</p><p>Specifically, TVL growth primarily stems from the migration of DeFi protocols and the deployment of new projects. For example, Decentralized Exchanges (DEXs) and lending platforms on Layer2 offer lower fees and faster transaction confirmations, attracting a large number of users. Community feedback indicates that the number of active addresses and transaction volume on Arbitrum and Optimism networks have also risen simultaneously, showing increased user participation. It is worth noting that TVL growth correlates with overall cryptocurrency market trends; for instance, during periods of price volatility for <a href="https://yayanews.cryptooptiontool.com/search?q=Bitcoin">Bitcoin</a> and Ethereum, Layer2 networks have demonstrated greater resilience, becoming venues for capital hedging and value appreciation.</p><p>Regarding data sources, besides DeFiLlama, platforms like CoinGecko also provide similar TVL tracking, but these figures should be viewed as dynamic indicators rather than precise predictions. Investors should note that TVL can be influenced by market sentiment, technical upgrades, and regulatory events. Overall, the TVL surge for Arbitrum and Optimism reflects growing market confidence in Ethereum scaling solutions and lays the groundwork for further ecosystem development.</p><h2>Ecosystem Development: A Landscape of Prosperity in DeFi and NFT</h2><p>The explosion of the Layer2 ecosystem is evident not only in data but also in practical applications. Arbitrum and Optimism have become crucial deployment platforms for DeFi and NFT projects, driving prosperity across the entire cryptocurrency ecosystem.</p><h3>Deep Integration in the DeFi Ecosystem</h3><p>In the DeFi space, Layer2 networks unlock more innovative possibilities by reducing transaction costs and increasing speed. Numerous well-known protoc